events.name: Ruby Tea Party
events.description: Our goal is to make the Ruby on Rails community in Singapore more inclusive for women and other minorities - so if you know anyone that codes or that you think would enjoy learning to code, invite them along!

events.name: JS Beginner Study Group
events.description:
- The purpose of this study group is for learning JS at your own pace, by working through resources, sharing and discussion - We do not host any talks or courses 


We will break out into 2 groups: • Group 1) For those who want to discuss "You Don't Know JS: this & Object Prototypes" - Chapters 1 & 2 (available at http://bit.ly/1KhU76p) • Group 2) For those who would rather work on their own material/practical projects/online resources instead, or go through questions with the group 



**DON'T FORGET to bring your laptops!! If you are joining the book discussion, please try to do your reading before the session! <3<3<3 **Join our chat channel: #milo-dinosaur on Kopi.JS Slack  http://kopijs.herokuapp.com/
events.location: Auston Institute, 50 Ophir Road, Level 3, Room 3-5, Singapore
